1. The agreement

This End User License Agreement ("Agreement") is between Yaw Labs ("Yaw Labs",
"we", "us") and the individual or entity ("you", "Licensee") who has purchased
access to the Yaw Labs course materials ("Course Materials"). By accessing the
Course Materials -- whether through a GitHub collaborator invitation, a
download link, or any other mechanism -- you accept this Agreement.

2. License grant

Subject to the terms below, Yaw Labs grants you a non-exclusive,
non-transferable, revocable, single-user license to:

  (a) Access, view, and study the Course Materials for your own personal
      learning.

  (b) Apply the techniques, patterns, and disciplines demonstrated in the
      Course Materials to your own work, including commercial work that you
      ship under your own name.

  (c) Quote brief excerpts of the Course Materials in your own writing, talks,
      or commentary, with the source clearly attributed to Yaw Labs and the
      excerpt no longer than is necessary to make a point.

3. Restrictions

You may not:

  (a) Redistribute, mirror, repost, or share the Course Materials -- in whole
      or in substantial part -- with anyone who has not separately purchased
      access. This applies to public posting (GitHub, websites, social media,
      video platforms, file shares) and private sharing (sending materials to a
      colleague, family member, or friend).

  (b) Share your access credentials or your GitHub account's access to the
      course repository. Each license is for one human licensee.

  (c) Sell, sublicense, rent, or otherwise transfer your license to a third
      party.

  (d) Remove or alter copyright notices, attribution lines, or this Agreement.

  (e) Use the Course Materials to train any model, AI system, or automated
      tool that reproduces or substantially imitates the Course Materials'
      content.

  (f) Use the Course Materials to create a competing course, book, or training
      product.

4. Reservation of rights

Yaw Labs retains all right, title, and interest in the Course Materials,
including all intellectual property rights. This Agreement does not transfer
any ownership rights to you.

5. Term and termination

This Agreement begins when you first access the Course Materials and continues
until terminated. It terminates automatically if:

  (a) You materially breach this Agreement.

  (b) You receive a refund or chargeback for your purchase.

  (c) Yaw Labs discontinues the course.

Upon termination, Yaw Labs may revoke your access (including removing you as a
GitHub collaborator) and you must cease use of the Course Materials and
destroy any local copies. Sections 4, 6, 7, 8, 9, and 10 survive termination.

6. Updates

Yaw Labs may update the Course Materials from time to time. Updates are
